reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 9, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Darling pacifier loved by baby
reviews.reviewText: I love this sweet, little rubber pacifier. I wanted a pacifier that didn’t have any pictures or logos, so that when baby inevitably was fussy for pictures and required a binky, the shots wouldn’t be too distracting. This pacifier is darling and fit the bill! Additionally my daughter loves it! It might be her favorite paci now. I think it’s because it’s a little bit bigger than some brands but I couldn’t say for sure why she likes it, just that she does! It’s all one solid piece, which I also love since it’s easy to clean and I don’t have to worry about mold getting in cracks or crevices.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality natural rubber Binky!
reviews.reviewText: I love these pacifiers! We have ordered three and each time the quality was excellent. They come in a cute bag and have clear instructions included on how to care for your pacifier . I was a little hesitant to try these pacifiers, because There were no Amazon reviews on them, but I decided to give them a shot because they were a lower price point for a natural rubber pacifier. I have been so happy with them. The bulb of the pacifier is a little bit large, so my baby gagged a little bit the first few times we tried it out. She quickly got the hang of it, and I actually feel like it stays in her mouth better than other types of pacifiers do. She has always had a strong suck and does great with a Soothie. We have been very happy with this purchase Knowing that she’s not sucking on cheap, and potentially harmful plastic chemicals, all day long.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Comparable to itzy ritzy
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for an all-rubber, one-piece alternative to the itzy ritzy rubber paci’s. I tried the natursutten 0-6, however, the teat was much smaller on those and my baby didn’t take to them (probably good for a newborn baby.) The 0-6 month rounded Sweetie pacifiers are the perfect replacement for Itzy Ritzy!I will say the rubber smell is stronger in these pacifiers than the other rubber ones I’ve tried, however, if you wash with soap and water prior to and after boiling, it fades quickly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars In love! Tough binky!
reviews.reviewText: My little boy is almost 3yrs old and autistic, so he needs his pacifier longer than most kids. This one is great because it's thick and sturdy rubber so it can take it rough 😂 my son chews it and tugs on it as well as binks with it and it holds up strong. We used tommee tippee before these and they are great for actual infants but the silicone is easily punctured and can't withstand any wear and tear. Highly reccomend for older babies like 1yr+ who start to chew on their binky but still need the comfort.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Love that it is all natural. My baby will only take this pacifier and natursutten paci. You can tell she likes the natursutten the best as she latches to it the quickest. BUT this is a close second. It’s not as soft as the natursutten but I’m glad my baby takes it. Must buy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 6, 2018
reviews.reviewText: We have tried countless brands.. my son would take a soothie but couldnt keep it in his mouth and he likes the old school Gerber rounded bulb paci but I like that these are one piece. Opened the little bag.. followed the simple instructions of boiling and it was ready to use. No crazy smells.. it does have a slight rubber smell if you stick your nose straight to at first but what else can someone expect of an all natural rubber paci (I've read tons of reviews complaining of a rubber smell from a rubber paci 😂) it's very soft and more pliable that a regular silicone paci. Another plus is it's a tad cheaper than some of the other brands of natural rubber paci's.. My son took this instantly and loves it! We will be buying more!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2021
reviews.reviewText: It’s adorable, and I’m sure it’s a great binky but the thing stinks! It has the oddest smell. It’s very offensive. My toddler even reacted to it. I don’t understand why it has to smell like that, I’ve had pacifiers made of the same materials and they never smelled like this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: We love this pacifier! It’s the only one my son doesn’t spit out besides the bibs but I didn’t want the plastic on his face all the time. So this is the perfect one!
Since I bought this one my baby love it. He doesn't like the other ones.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on November 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Washes well and lasts. Highly recommended

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on May 18, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Very large, so we had to order the smaller size. The 6-12 month one is an ideal size for a dummy. 12-18 is more like a over used 'favourite' dummy, that needs to be thrown away because the teat has expanded so much. However it is very thick, unlike the over used 'favourite' one. The 6-12 one has helped our son successfully disown the old favourite 'bibs' dummy. Its also not as thick as the 12-18 one. I would recommend. They are easier to clean, and you don't have the worry of the teat coming away from the plastic.
Held up to a lot of use by our daughter. Not flashy by any means but it seemed a ton better made than the drugstore ones everyone else uses.
